#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:18
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:21
msgid ""
"This controller is a class compliant USB MIDI and audio device, so it can be"
" used without any special drivers on GNU/Linux, Mac OS X, and Windows. "
"However, if you wish to use the {ref}`ASIO sound API <preferences-sound-"
"api>` under Windows, please install the latest driver package available from"
" the [Support "
"page](https://support.hercules.com/en/product/djcontrolinpulse500-en//)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:27
msgid "Sound card setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:30
msgid ""
"This controller has built-in 4 channel output sound card, with MAIN output "
"(2x RCA or 2x unbalanced 6.35mm jack) and HEADPHONE output (stereo 3.5mm "
"jack or stereo 6.35mm jack)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:34
msgid "Open **Preferences > Sound Hardware**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:35
msgid "Select the **Output** tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:36
msgid ""
"From the **Main** drop-down menu, select the audio interface, then "
"**Channels 1-2**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:38
msgid ""
"From the **Headphones** drop-down menu, select the audio interface, then "
"**Channels 3-4**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:40
msgid "Click **Apply** to save the changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:43
msgid ""
"The {ref}`example setups section <setup-laptop-and-external-card>` provides "
"more details about the audio configuration in Mixxx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_inpulse_500.md:46
msgid ""
"The **Master** and **Headphone** knobs, as well as the **Master** button are"
" hardware controls and interact directly with the integrated sound card’s "
"output. Although they also send MIDI messages, they have NOT been mapped in "
"Mixxx, so do not expect an on-screen reaction when using them. This was done"
" to prevent the knobs to adjust both the gain on the controller’s sound card"
" and in Mixxx."
msgstr ""

